The paper deals with list decoding algorithms for algebraic geometric (AG) codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes used in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of Gröbner bases, which are a tool from computational algebraic geometry, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses unique decoding algorithms, which are related to decoding algorithms for error-correcting codes, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves computational optimization, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
